snippet.textDisplay: This is what I was missing from my life—thank you! Bengali folk song meets Afrobeats! To me, internationalization does not mean creating a space where white people get a taste of diversity or feel good about themselves by seeking innocence. I envision an internationalization space where we, people who have endured (and continue to endure) the pain of colonization, connect and cultivate joy.

snippet.textDisplay: Bolai bahullo Bangla nobo borso ebong er oitihjjho k samne rekhe ganti kora but abaro ekoi somossa Bangla uccharon nea, sorry to say Ornob er Bangla uccharon ekebarei osposto, jeno ganta gun gunea tar nejer jonnoi gaiche, onne na bujhleo chole kingba Bangla subtitle dekhe neo, lucky that Bangla subtitle was there otherwise i hardly understood what Ornob was singing, Bangla uccaron e odhik monojogi howa dorkar...sorry it may seem rude and harsh but the reality is that....Our Bangla should be Highlighted with it's purity in pronunciation to make it more and more glorified.
